    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-04-25T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-04-25T15:00:00-05:00" n="307"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                <head>307. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Mission at the United
                        Nations</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d307fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 674.84A/4–2556. Limited Official Use; Priority. Received at 3:57
                        p.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-04-25T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1956—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>887. Re: Palestine. Letter from <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> to <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> Pres,<note n="2" xml:id="d307fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Henry Cabot Lodge, Jr.</persName>
                    </note> signed in Jerusalem on April 18, transmitted by Cordier today (copies
                    being pouched).<note n="3" xml:id="d307fn3">Not printed. (Department of State,
                        Central Files, 674.84A/4–2556)</note> After referring to unconditional
                    assurances Egypt and Israel re compliance Article II, para 2 of <gloss
                        target="#t_GAA1">GAA</gloss>,<note n="4" xml:id="d307fn4">See <ref
                            target="#d297">Document 297</ref>.</note> letter states:</p>
                <p>“In support of the measures ensuring compliance with Article II, para 2, of which
                    I have thus been notified, I have put before the two governments proposals for a
                    strengthening of the observer activities, including the establishment of a
                    number of fixed <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> observation posts on both
                    sides of the demarcation line in the Gaza area and occasional <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> mobile patrols along the demarcation line. I hope
                    within a few days to be able to inform you about the arrangements to be
                    established. In principle, the proposals have already been accepted by the two
                    governments concerned.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Lodge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
